                        "type": "0",
                        "version": 0,
                        "content": "The nurse is creating a plan of care for a client with an autistic disorder. A behavior modification approach (operant conditioning) is being used to improve communication. Which would the nurse include in the plan of care?",
                        "subjectId": "ad5ab04c79144c0ea9b83385308c3b1d",
                        "difficultyIds": "49d86bb4d5071eb7de614d6c79f7abfb",
                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Creating创新",
                        "textAnalysis": "Rationale:\nOperant conditioning entails rewarding a client for desired behaviors and is the basis for behavior modification. It uses a positive reinforcement approach. None of the remaining options are characteristics or appropriate components of the plan of care for this form of therapy.\n\nClient Needs: Psychosocial Integrity\nClinical Judgment/Cognitive Skill(s): Generate Solutions\nCognitive Ability: Creating\nContent Area: Mental Health\nHealth Problem: Mental Health: Neurodevelopmental Disorders\nIntegrated Process: Nursing Process/Planning\nPriority Concepts: Stress and Coping, Communication\nStrategies: Subject\n\nTest-Taking Strategy:\nFocus on the subject, operant conditioning, and use knowledge of the definition of operant conditioning to answer the question. Specific knowledge of the characteristics of this form of behavior modification will easily direct you to the correct option.\n ",
                        "id": "906fc778e304402ba2d89ec740f62cfc",
